raw_data.owner_title: Night Swim Coffee - One Wells Fargo

reviews_data.review_text: To the person working this morning that made me a maple cardamom latte before opening, you’re amazing, the coffee was amazing, and I made it to my meeting on time because of you. Thank you!
Bayley, Tiffany, and Lina killing the game!
Best cappuccino in uptown Charlotte.
Fabulous matcha, love their cardamom syrup, and the baristas are gems🩷
Finally delicious cappuccino in the city! Also nice services.
They make a fine Americano here. Great shop. Great location, on the second floor.

I’ve been coming here for almost 2 years now, and I love it. Tiffany and Bayley are probably some of the friendliest and most talented barista duo I’ve met. I’ve seen them work incredibly well together and this is the first time I realized how much the skill of a barista can change how good your coffee is.

Over the past 2 years I’ve usually rotated between these orders (all with whole milk): Brown Sugar Vanilla Latte, Mocha Latte, Maple Cardamom Latte (current favorite), Matcha Latte (unsweetened), or Brown Sugar Vanilla Cappuccino (2nd favorite).

I never give 5 star reviews but for Night Swim, I will.  What a genuine pleasure.  I want to pack them Up and take the whole place to my home state...Or perhaps I'll just have to move to Charlotte.  Great coffee nicely presented by a talented friendly barista.
Great experience, delicious coffee!
Smooth coffee with cream and sugar. Tint of lemon flavor. Friendly staff.
Great place. Very pleasant staff. Good location and seating area. Very good espresso. Will def visit again. 5 stars.

beware of their Matcha tea Latte with almond milk. After two sips I felt nauseous but didn't pay attention to it thinking I just needed some morning caffeine boost. After few more sips I had sharp pain in my stomach & started throwing up. I've never had such a violent reaction to any beverage before, I think either match, ice or almond milk or all were contaminated. I felt better after throwing up all of the matcha I drank from them.
Great espresso/ coffee shop in downtown Charlotte...2nd floor of wellsfargo.  Cool atmosphere,  friendly baristas, fantastic espresso drinks.
Great espresso drinks. Happy to have found this place while visiting NC last week.
FANTASTIC COFFEE! As a personally acclaimed professional coffee taster, this is the best place to get coffee.

What a great place for afternoon coffee or actually anytime coffee! Great cold brew and amazing lattes along with the city’s most efficient, friendly and remarkably well managed baristas. I would be remiss in not extolling the merits of their seasonal drinks, my favorite was the refreshing Sunrise from the Summer menu, which had to be created by a beverage genius. So, take the over-the-street walkway or the escalator to the brightly lit and inviting Night Swim Coffee in the One Wells Fargo building, you won’t regret it.

This is a must-stop for me every work day I'm in the office. Love the coffee of course but the prompt and friendly baristas always make my first cup of Joe a joy. Whenever I get a pastry those are good too.
Thanks!
👍
Probably the best coffee beans you can find in NC. I got the maple cardamom latte with oat milk and it was so good that I wish their cups were bigger.
Good and small coffee shop with amazing lattes. Friendly service!
Great coffee, convenient location, good service!
Grabbed a coffee before going into work! Amazing coffee and they were quick! Would recommend to support small business!

Best coffee in Charlotte for me! Just surpassed Community Matters Cafe.

Got the creamiest cappucino, love it!!
Very decent coffee. Nice flavor.

Nice little coffee shop located in One Wells Fargo Center on the second floor! Has teas and lattés, vegan options in the bakery, and non dairy milk alternatives! Nice seating area nearby with a sunlight and a view!
Very nice coffee shop in the One Wells Fargo building. Specialty coffee and teas. On this day I had a black tea. Very good. Modern shop. Recommend.
